#### Feature Description

Let's say we have a generic component containing some standard menu items, and we want to allow users of this component to add their own custom menu items. There is no way to add "external" menu-items as proper children of the "internal" menu.

The problem is described in this SO: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/59629093/insert-menu-items-using-ng-content

#### Use Case

If `mat-menu-items` are provided as `<ng-content>` to the component defining the `<mat-menu>`, the items are detached from the `<mat-menu>`

Preferably I would like angular material to just fix this, but if this is problematic I propose the following. Given:
```
  // The matMenu all the items should be connected to
  @ViewChild('actionsMenu', {static: false}) actionsMenu: MatMenu;

  // The matMenuItem's inserted into this component externally
  @ContentChildren(MatMenuItem) menuItems: QueryList<MatMenuItem>;
```

I would like to loop over these `menuItems` and attach them to the given `actionsMenu`. I would expect the `actionsMenu.addItem(item)` to do this, but the attached items are all without a parentMenu after I try this. And for given menu-items with submenus, the `_triggersSubmenu` is always false.

